    <summary>Windows right-click menu path copy tool with four path formats</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
# WinCopath

A Windows right-click menu path copy tool. Adds a "Win Copath" option to the context menu of files and folders, supporting four path formats for copying.

## Features

Right-click on a file or folder to display the "Win Copath" submenu, which contains four options:

- `/ (Forward Slash)` — `C:/Users/test/file.txt`
- `\ (Backslash)` — `C:\Users\test\file.txt`
- `"/" (Quoted Forward Slash)` — `"C:/Users/test/file.txt"`
- `"\\" (Quoted Backslash)` — `"C:\\Users\\test\\file.txt"`

## Usage

After installation, the right-click menu will NOT be modified by default. You need to enable it manually (run PowerShell as Administrator):

```
wcpath on     # Add Win Copath to the right-click menu
wcpath off    # Remove Win Copath from the right-click menu
wcpath help   # Show help
```

## Notes

- Requires Windows 10 or later
- Requires administrator privileges to modify the registry
- The registry design references PowerShell 7 and uses `ExtendedSubCommandsKey` to share the submenu definition
]]></description>
